title: Get Customer
name: GetCustomer
description: Route which returns customer information.

title: Check Login
name: LoginCustomer
description: Route for validating the login of a Customer.

Success 200.description: Tells if Users login form is correct. If this is false don't allow user to log into the app.

Token returned from Service. Used by the backend to identify a user. Store this, because it is needed for identifying a registered user in subsequent rest calls. Returns -1 if validation was unsuccessful.

title: Register Customer
name: RegisterCustomer
description: Route for registration of a new Customer.

Parameter.description: Raw password of the user to register.
Unique Email of the user to register.

Success 200.description: Token returned from Service. Used by the backend to identify a user. Store this, because it is needed for identifying a registered user in subsequent rest calls.

title: Accept Booking Request
name: AcceptBookingRequest
description: Route for accepting a Lift-Request made by a other user.

Parameter.description: ID of the user, who has sent the booking request.
ID of the lift, the user has sent a booking request for.

Success 200.description: True, if Booking Acception was rejected, else false.
If rejected is true, here is the reason why it was rejected.

title: Delete Booking
name: DeleteBooking
description: Route for deleting a Booking-Request of a user.

Parameter.description: ID of the user, who wants to delete the booking of a lift.
ID of the lift, the user wants to delete the booking from.

title: Get Cities
name: GetCities
description: Route for getting all cities for a specified federal state.

Parameter.description: Name of the federal state. Valid state names are returned from the Get States Route.

Success 200.description: List containing all cities of the state.
Name of the federal state, which the city belongs to.

title: Get Faculties
name: GetFaculties
description: Route for getting all faculties of OTH Regensburg.

Success 200.description: List containing all faculties of OTH Regensburg.

title: Get States
name: GetFederalStates
description: Route for getting all federal states of Germany.

title: Get Post Input
name: GetPostInput
description: Route for getting Lift-Requests of a user.

Success 200.description: ID of the lift the user wants to book.
ID of the user, who wants to book the lift.
Name of the user, who wants to book the lift.
Contact Email of the user, who wants to book the lift.
True, if user is invited to the lift.
ID of the event of the lift. Null, if lift is a private trip.
Name of the event of the lift. Null, if lift is a private trip.

title: Get Post Output
name: GetPostOutput
description: Route for getting Booking-Requests sent by the specified user to other users.

Success 200.description: Array of Booking-Request sent from the specified user to other users.
ID of the lift the user wants to book.
ID of the user, who advertised the lift.
Name of the user, who advertised the lift.
Contact Email of the user, who advertised the lift.
True, if user is invited to the lift.
ID of the event of the lift. Null, if lift is a private trip.
Name of the event of the lift. Null, if lift is a private trip.

title: Get Recommended Price
name: GetRecommendedPrice
description: Route for getting the recommended price for a lift advertisement. Based on distance and number of passengers. Distance calculated by Vincenty Algorithm.

title: Post Booking
name: PostBooking
description: Route for posting a Booking Request on a specified Lift by a specified user.

Parameter.description: ID of the user, who wants to book the lift.
ID of the lift, the user wants to book.

title: Post Lift
name: PostLift
description: Route for posting a new Lift.

Parameter.description: Object containing information about the lift to post.
ID of the user who wants to post the lift.
Event for which the lift is advertised. Can also be null.
List of faculties, for which the event is interesting.
String representing the date of the lift. Format: DDMMYYYY.

title: Refuse Booking Request
name: RefuseBookingRequest
description: Route for refusing Booking-Requests from a other user.

Parameter.description: ID of the user, who has sent the booking request.
ID of the lift, the user has sent a booking request for.

title: Search Lifts
name: SearchLifts
description: Route for getting Lift Recommendations specified through a submitted search request.

Parameter.description: String representing the date of the lift. Format: DDMMYYYY.
True, if user wants to search for lifts to events. False, if user wants to search for private lifts.
Events interesting for the specified Faculties, should be searched.
Radius Search for lifts within the specified radius.

Success 200.description: Array containing lifts fulfilling the search request.
ID of the Advertiser of the lift.
Name of the Avertiser of the lift.
Email of the Advertiser of the lift.
Description of the Event of the lift.
Title of the Event of the Lift.
Faculties, for which the Lift is interesting. Null, if lift reason is a private trip.

title: Delete All Likes
name: DeleteAllLikes
description: Route for deleting all likes or dislikes for a specified User.

Parameter.description: ID of the logged in user. Is at the moment the userId, which was returned from the backend during the login.

Success 200.description: True, if deleting the Like was successful.

title: Delete Like
name: DeleteLike
description: Route for deleting likes or dislikes for a specified Meal

Parameter.description: User ID of the logged in user.
ID of the meal to like or dislike

Success 200.description: True, if deleting the Like was successful.

title: Get All Likes of Customer
name: GetAllLikes
description: Route for getting all Meals which a specified user liked or dislikes.

Success 200.description: State of the user. 0: neutral. 1: likes the meal. -1: dislikes the meal.
Total number of likes of the specified meal.
Total number of dislikes of the specified meal.

title: Get Like State
name: GetLikeState
description: Route for getting number of likes and dislikes of a specified meal. It also returns the status of the user, which explains if user likes / dislikes or is neutral (not liked, but also not disliked) to the specified Meal.

Success 200.description: State of the user. 0: neutral. 1: likes the meal. -1: dislikes the meal.
Total number of likes of the specified meal.
Total number of dislikes of the specified meal.

title: Get Mensa Meals
name: GetMeals
description: Route for getting meals for a specified date.

Parameter.description: Day of current week. Valid Params: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr.

Success 200.description: List of meals for the specified date.

title: Get Most Popular and Unpopular Meal
name: GetMostPopular
description: Route for getting the most popular Meal and the most unpopular Meal of the specified Date.

Parameter.description: Day of current week. Valid Params: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr.

Success 200.description: Rank of the meal regarding its likes.
Rank of the meal regarding its dislikes.

title: Post Like
name: PostLike
description: Route for posting likes or dislikes for a specified Meal.

Parameter.description: ID of the meal to like or dislike

Success 200.description: True, if posting the Like was successful.
